1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:04,671
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:04,754 --> 00:00:09,050
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:10,593
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:12,971
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i>
<i>In the tangle</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:19,185
[Karla] Brother Atoy!
Did you find Ibyang's parents?

7
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:21,604
[Atoy] <i>Sorry, Ibyang. I was wrong.</i>

8
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:23,690
<i>The person didn't know your parents.</i>

9
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:25,150
[Ame] <i>Sister Norma is gone?</i>

10
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:27,777
[Atoy] <i>She handed this to me</i>
<i>before she passed away.</i>

11
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:28,862
[Ame] Martin?

12
00:00:28,945 --> 00:00:30,697
Does that mean he's Ibyang's father?

13
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:33,491
I don't know if that's
a first name or a surname.

14
00:00:34,159 --> 00:00:35,660
[Atoy] <i>I'll never know.</i>

15
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,787
[Martina] <i>We'll look for a child</i>
<i>the same age as Audrey's daughter</i>

16
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:40,832
[in English] And then, we'll convince
the parents to hand over their child.

17
00:00:40,915 --> 00:00:42,292
[Ibyang] <i>Aren't you leaving?</i>

18
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:43,668
Why? Are you asking me to leave?

19
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:46,504
[Ibyang] <i>I just need to buy</i>
<i>something at the store.</i>

20
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:48,506
Ibyang! Hi!

21
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:49,466
‪PREVIOUSLY

22
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:51,217
Aunt Audrey!

23
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:52,677
[Atoy] <i>Where's the place with…</i>

24
00:00:52,761 --> 00:00:55,346
<i>yellow fresh paint?</i>

25
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:58,349
Ah, I painted some benches in the park.

26
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:00,935
I wish my child were as kind as you.

27
00:01:01,519 --> 00:01:02,812
Why?

28
00:01:02,896 --> 00:01:04,189
Is he naughty?

29
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:07,609
I'm just sad because I'm not with her now.

30
00:01:07,692 --> 00:01:11,988
It feels like we both have drama in life.

31
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:14,407
Isn't your mother with you now?

32
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:16,034
Kind of.

33
00:01:16,117 --> 00:01:17,202
[sobs]

34
00:01:18,495 --> 00:01:20,955
[Atoy] <i>This child already knows</i>
<i>how to skip class.</i>

35
00:01:33,218 --> 00:01:35,220
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

36
00:01:36,137 --> 00:01:40,183
Can I call you Mama Mary?

37
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:41,434
[chuckles]

38
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:43,728
- You're really funny!
- [bright music playing]

39
00:01:43,812 --> 00:01:46,648
Who did you inherit
that way of speaking from?

40
00:01:46,731 --> 00:01:48,900
You always make me laugh.

41
00:01:48,983 --> 00:01:51,820
- But I'm not trying to be funny.
- [Audrey] Ah.

42
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:54,197
You really look like Mama Mary.

43
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,490
[chuckles]

44
00:01:59,327 --> 00:02:04,916
[phone ringing]

45
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:09,838
[quirky music playing]

46
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:14,008
Oh, is someone looking for you?

47
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:16,636
[Audrey] Uh…

48
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:20,348
[Audrey] Why?

49
00:02:20,431 --> 00:02:22,183
[in English] Um, my dad just called.

50
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:23,351
[in English] Is everything okay?

51
00:02:23,434 --> 00:02:26,354
Ah, maybe it's important!

52
00:02:26,437 --> 00:02:27,814
Um…

53
00:02:27,897 --> 00:02:29,440
Maybe it's important.

54
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:32,527
- [Audrey] Oh?
- We can meet again next time.

55
00:02:32,610 --> 00:02:33,778
All right, all right. Yes.

56
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:36,698
It's fine. I'm busy too…

57
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:39,367
But I'm happy we met.

58
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:40,702
Ah.

59
00:02:40,785 --> 00:02:42,287
Me too.

60
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:45,206
Um, finish your porridge, okay?

61
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,417
I'll take care of the cookies.

62
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,334
‪[Audrey] Ah.

63
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:50,795
- See you!
- [Audrey] See you.

64
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:52,547
[chuckles softly]

65
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:54,632
[sentimental music playing]

66
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:17,530
[music fades]

67
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:22,911
[suave theme music playing]

68
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:26,331
[motorcycle revving]

69
00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:27,749
[sewing machine whirring]

70
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:29,208
[scratches]

71
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:30,793
[snipping]

72
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:31,753
[clicking]

73
00:03:31,836 --> 00:03:34,130
[sewing machine whirring]

74
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:36,382
[gunshots blasting]

75
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:38,384
[gunshots blasting]

76
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:40,720
[clicking]

77
00:03:40,803 --> 00:03:42,347
[snipping]

78
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:44,015
[electronic blipping]

79
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:50,855
[music fades]

80
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:58,279
[sneaky music playing ]

81
00:04:05,286 --> 00:04:06,746
[music fades]

82
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:07,914
[gasps]

83
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:11,584
[whispering] I'm in trouble.

84
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:15,129
[quirky music playing]

85
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:17,799
Hmm.

86
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:23,471
And when did you learn how to skip class?

87
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:25,098
Huh?

88
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:29,102
Looks like you even planned it.

89
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:32,647
No, I didn't.

90
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:35,733
What do you mean no? Oh, what's this?

91
00:04:35,817 --> 00:04:38,361
Oh, huh? What is that? What's that?

92
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:40,780
You even changed clothes.

93
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:43,032
Who taught you those tricks, huh?

94
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:44,701
From you!

95
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:47,120
I disguised myself too.

96
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:50,415
[in English] Disguise, disguise.
Now you're blaming me.

97
00:04:50,498 --> 00:04:52,500
Ibyang, what's wrong with you?

98
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:55,878
You shouldn't skip class or cut class.

99
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,631
How will you learn if you
don't attend your classes?

100
00:04:58,715 --> 00:05:00,550
Come on. Let's go back.

101
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:03,428
But the kids there are bullies.

102
00:05:03,511 --> 00:05:06,431
They tease me that I don't have parents.

103
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:08,683
[melancholic music playing]

104
00:05:08,766 --> 00:05:09,976
[Atoy sighs]

105
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:12,395
Ibyang…

106
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:15,273
I promise you.

107
00:05:16,232 --> 00:05:20,194
I promise I'll find your parents.

108
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:21,112
Okay?

109
00:05:21,904 --> 00:05:25,241
But for now, we're going back to school.

110
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,951
I'll handle those bullies.
I'll talk to them.

111
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:28,411
Come on!

112
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:29,996
Don't, Master.

113
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:32,498
They'll just tease me more.

114
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:33,458
[scoffs]

115
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:34,917
No, I'll--

116
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:37,045
What's that?

117
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:38,838
Oh?

118
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:42,050
Wow! What's this? Cookies.

119
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:45,136
Where did this come from?
I didn't pack this for you.

120
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,929
Where did you get it?

121
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:48,848
I have a new friend.

122
00:05:49,515 --> 00:05:51,434
Friend? Really?

123
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:53,019
- Give it back to me. Give it back!
- Psst.

124
00:05:53,811 --> 00:05:55,188
Hey, what's wrong with you?

125
00:05:55,271 --> 00:05:56,939
Ibyang, don't you think?

126
00:05:57,023 --> 00:06:01,527
You can't just accept
random things from strangers,

127
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:02,570
especially food.

128
00:06:02,653 --> 00:06:04,072
Who gave this to you?

129
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:07,533
But it's my friend who gave it.

130
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:10,286
And she's kind.

131
00:06:10,369 --> 00:06:11,954
Friend, kind?

132
00:06:12,955 --> 00:06:14,582
Kidnappers are like that too.

133
00:06:14,665 --> 00:06:16,876
Kind at first, then they take you.

134
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:19,003
Come on. Let's go back to school.

135
00:06:20,254 --> 00:06:23,091
[music concludes]

136
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:26,302
[birds chirping]

137
00:06:29,388 --> 00:06:32,225
Have you seen the names on the list?

138
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:37,105
Yes. I've already seen two of them, but…

139
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:38,981
they live far away.

140
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:40,900
It's easy to find them on social media.

141
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:42,485
[mysterious music playing]

142
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:44,654
[in English] So it looks like
this last kid is our only hope.

143
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:47,240
[in English] Good thing
I already have the address.

144
00:06:47,323 --> 00:06:48,866
[in English] I'm gonna pay them a visit.

145
00:06:50,034 --> 00:06:51,452
- [blows raspberry]
- [Martina, in English] What?

146
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:53,454
[in English] You don't like my plan?

147
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:57,834
Hmm, this is too much hassle
just because of Audrey.

148
00:06:58,876 --> 00:07:00,253
What can we do?

149
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:02,588
[in English] Just think about it this way.

150
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:03,923
[in English] We're not
doing this for Audrey.

151
00:07:04,006 --> 00:07:05,383
[in English] We're doing this for Dad.

152
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:08,886
So we can please him
and ask for favors someday.

153
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:10,138
[in English] Right?

154
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:12,181
[in English] Yeah.

155
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:14,475
[music fades]

156
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:15,852
Ah, I'm sorry, ma'am.

157
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:18,354
Ibyang ran a bit late. We had…

158
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,815
We had a family emergency at home.

159
00:07:20,898 --> 00:07:22,525
We had to take care of something.

160
00:07:22,608 --> 00:07:23,901
It's fine.

161
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,736
She'll just catch up later
with the lessons.

162
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:26,696
[Atoy] All right, then.

163
00:07:27,363 --> 00:07:28,698
I'll leave her with you.

164
00:07:29,824 --> 00:07:32,452
[muffled chatter]

165
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:34,912
There.

166
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:37,790
Don't ever do that again, okay?

167
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:38,833
That's dangerous.

168
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:40,751
I know you want friends.

169
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:44,297
But don't ever do that again, okay?
It's dangerous!

170
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:46,174
Okay?

171
00:07:48,384 --> 00:07:49,635
I'm sorry.

172
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:52,847
Um, it won't happen again.

173
00:07:53,514 --> 00:07:57,185
[upbeat rock music playing]

174
00:07:57,727 --> 00:07:58,853
Hey, Ibyang!

175
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:05,234
You even brought your neighbor
to pretend to be your father.

176
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:09,530
What did you just say?

177
00:08:12,909 --> 00:08:14,285
I am her father.

178
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:26,214
[scoffs] Oh, really?

179
00:08:26,297 --> 00:08:28,966
But last time you said
you weren't her father.

180
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:29,967
Liar.

181
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:33,554
You're just as much
a liar as your neighbor!

182
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:36,724
Oh, come on. And you believed my joke!

183
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,852
Doesn't your dad joke around with you?

184
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,145
Oh?

185
00:08:41,812 --> 00:08:43,981
She doesn't really have a father.

186
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:45,816
Janine is adopted.

187
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:46,859
That's not true.

188
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:47,944
Stop it!

189
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:58,037
[bright music playing]

190
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,830
Thank you.

191
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:00,790
It was just a joke.

192
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:02,667
No, just kidding.

193
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,919
Now she won't bully you anymore.

194
00:09:05,002 --> 00:09:05,836
Are you okay now?

195
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:12,134
See?

196
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:14,845
[speaking in Visayan] You can be prettier!

197
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:16,097
What are you saying, Sis Tonet?

198
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:17,265
Ah, nothing.

199
00:09:17,348 --> 00:09:19,058
I said, you're beautiful.

200
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:20,810
I'm excited for you, Karla!

201
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:22,144
- Me too!
- [both giggle]

202
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:24,897
You know, I really feel it.

203
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:27,984
I really, really feel
that Gavin will confess to me.

204
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:30,736
Especially when I encouraged him

205
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:33,155
to be honest about his feelings.

206
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:34,865
[Karla exclaims]

207
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:37,326
I said it's not good to waste time,

208
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:40,955
especially when it comes to love!

209
00:09:41,038 --> 00:09:42,081
- [giggles]
- Right!

210
00:09:42,164 --> 00:09:45,459
That's real love!
That's right. Just keep manifesting.

211
00:09:45,543 --> 00:09:47,295
[bright music playing]

212
00:09:47,378 --> 00:09:48,754
[Tonet] Oh.

213
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:50,756
Is this okay?

214
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:54,176
It's perfect. You look so beautiful.

215
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:58,097
Isn't it too obvious that
I put on makeup just to meet him?

216
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,348
[Tonet] Of course not!

217
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:01,851
Your makeup is so light,

218
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:02,935
he won't notice.

219
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:04,812
And besides, what's wrong with that?

220
00:10:04,895 --> 00:10:08,899
We girls should always fix ourselves up

221
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:11,944
when we go out,
so we're always presentable.

222
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:13,988
That's true, but…

223
00:10:14,864 --> 00:10:16,866
he knows this isn't my style.

224
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:18,117
That's fine!

225
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,036
This is just light makeup.

226
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:22,663
And you know the effect…

227
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:25,541
It's like he'll just look at you,
and then suddenly…

228
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:26,500
[gasps]

229
00:10:26,584 --> 00:10:27,501
…he's staring at you!

230
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:28,461
- [exclaims]
- [giggles]

231
00:10:28,544 --> 00:10:30,671
- That's how it is when you go natural!
- [upbeat music playing]

232
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:33,174
- Oh.
- Is this it? Sis?

233
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:34,884
Of course not!

234
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:37,386
We still need to dress up,
so he'll really be stunned by you!

235
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,471
[Karla] Sis, come on.

236
00:10:38,554 --> 00:10:40,681
That's too obvious!

237
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:42,642
Wearing dresses is not my style at all.

238
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:44,018
What do you want to wear then?

239
00:10:44,101 --> 00:10:45,311
A gown?

240
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:47,313
- Oh? Just natural.
- Overacting.

241
00:10:47,396 --> 00:10:49,023
[sneaky music playing]

242
00:10:49,106 --> 00:10:50,024
[exclaims]

243
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:54,278
She's here.

244
00:10:54,945 --> 00:10:56,113
Roma!

245
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:58,491
Roma, someone's looking for you!

246
00:11:00,117 --> 00:11:01,494
- Thank you.
- Ah, here.

247
00:11:01,577 --> 00:11:07,291
[suspicious music playing]

248
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:09,210
What's this?

249
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:11,712
You're Roma, right?

250
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:14,298
Yes.

251
00:11:14,382 --> 00:11:16,550
What is this, a census?

252
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:18,928
There was just a census last month.

253
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:20,304
No.

254
00:11:20,388 --> 00:11:22,973
I just have a question
about the child you adopted.

255
00:11:23,557 --> 00:11:24,934
What?!

256
00:11:25,017 --> 00:11:26,185
Oh, no!

257
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:29,397
Is that child in trouble at school again?

258
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,606
Why?

259
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:32,942
Is that adopted child a headache?

260
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:34,693
She's a pain in everything!

261
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:36,320
Especially for my wallet!

262
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:39,698
I said if I get called to school again,

263
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,867
I'll return her to the orphanage!

264
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:43,369
[chuckles]

265
00:11:43,452 --> 00:11:46,372
Why do you sound like
you regret adopting her?

266
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:48,874
I wasn't the one who wanted to adopt her.

267
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:51,919
It was my ex-husband!

268
00:11:52,002 --> 00:11:54,547
Well, I agreed because he had money,

269
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:56,257
but the shameless man!

270
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:58,342
He had another family!

271
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:01,220
So now, the child is under my care.

272
00:12:02,263 --> 00:12:05,558
What if I told you

273
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:07,977
I'm willing to pay a lot of money,

274
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:09,728
as long as you give me the child.

275
00:12:10,604 --> 00:12:12,690
[music fades]

276
00:12:13,607 --> 00:12:14,525
How much?

277
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:18,362
[tense music playing]

278
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:20,364
[Roma chuckles softly]

279
00:12:20,448 --> 00:12:22,992
I agree with your offer, ma'am.

280
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:26,579
[chuckles softly]

281
00:12:26,662 --> 00:12:28,706
But…

282
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:32,710
I want to be sure that…

283
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:35,296
I won't get into trouble.

284
00:12:35,379 --> 00:12:36,505
Because

285
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:39,842
if the child gets harmed under your care…

286
00:12:40,843 --> 00:12:41,886
I'll be the one blamed.

287
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:49,351
[in English] Uh, y-you… you don't need
to worry about… that.

288
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:51,187
Because the truth is,

289
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,856
we're the real family
of the child you adopted.

290
00:12:54,565 --> 00:12:56,525
But before, like you,

291
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:57,693
we were…

292
00:12:57,776 --> 00:12:59,361
you know… poor.

293
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:01,780
- [chuckles softly]
- Now that we're more well off,

294
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:03,741
we just want to take the child back.

295
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:04,617
[chuckles]

296
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:05,951
Ah, okay.

297
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:08,996
I'm easy to talk to, ma'am.

298
00:13:09,079 --> 00:13:09,914
[titters]

299
00:13:09,997 --> 00:13:11,749
But you know,

300
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:14,251
I've already spent so much on that child.

301
00:13:14,335 --> 00:13:17,004
- School, food, medicine, and--
- Don't worry.

302
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:20,424
Don't worry, because I'm willing to pay

303
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:22,760
for the last eight years
you've cared for her.

304
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:25,137
[chuckles]

305
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:26,514
[Martina, in English] Now…

306
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:34,104
[in English] Down payment.

307
00:13:36,148 --> 00:13:38,609
I'll pay you in full
once everything is done.

308
00:13:42,112 --> 00:13:43,572
[Roma gasps, chuckles]

309
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:45,074
[Roma] Ah… [clears throat]

310
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:48,035
[in English] Do we have a deal?

311
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:58,879
So, Mabel,

312
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:02,716
are you coming to the amusement park
Teacher mentioned?

313
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:06,136
Of course! I'm excited.

314
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:08,597
Later, when I get home,

315
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:10,641
I'll tell Mama right away.

316
00:14:10,724 --> 00:14:13,727
What about you, Janine?
Aren't you excited?

317
00:14:13,811 --> 00:14:15,980
But isn't it that if you don't
have a parent with you,

318
00:14:16,063 --> 00:14:17,398
you can't come?

319
00:14:18,983 --> 00:14:20,818
But your mother is there!

320
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:23,946
[Janine sighs] I already know
what she's going to say,

321
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:25,447
"More expenses!

322
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:26,866
It's always something I need to pay for."

323
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:28,909
[Audrey] Most bullies

324
00:14:28,993 --> 00:14:31,537
have problems at home

325
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:33,873
or with their own families.

326
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:38,210
That's why they take out
their anger at school

327
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,462
or on other people.

328
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:43,966
[gentle music playing]

329
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:46,760
Janine, didn't they say,

330
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:49,430
even if it's not a parent,

331
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:52,391
as long as you have
a chaperone, you can join?

332
00:14:52,474 --> 00:14:56,562
Do you want me to ask
my sisters to accompany you?

333
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:58,647
What are you trying to imply, huh?

334
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:02,109
That you're better than me
because you have more people to bring?

335
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,111
You're so full of yourself!

336
00:15:04,194 --> 00:15:07,072
[melancholic music playing]

337
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,617
Move aside, you show-off!

338
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,250
[Karla] Gavin!

339
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:20,002
[music fades]

340
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:21,378
What is it you wanted to tell me?

341
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:23,047
Well, it's--

342
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:24,965
[muffled chattering in distance]

343
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,383
Wait.

344
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:28,552
Are you wearing lipstick?

345
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:30,262
This?

346
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:31,889
- Yes.
- No!

347
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,474
It's nothing.

348
00:15:33,557 --> 00:15:34,558
I just ate bubble gum.

349
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:35,768
The "Pintoora" brand.

350
00:15:36,518 --> 00:15:38,896
Do you know that? Do you know "Pintoora"?

351
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:39,897
No.

352
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,315
What's that?

353
00:15:42,024 --> 00:15:43,734
- Wait, wait! Here.
- What?!

354
00:15:43,817 --> 00:15:45,277
- [grunts] What?!
- There!

355
00:15:45,361 --> 00:15:46,487
Your hand.

356
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:48,989
There!

357
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:51,325
You look better like that.

358
00:15:51,408 --> 00:15:54,954
[pleasant music playing]

359
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:59,333
You know, Karla, I was going
to confess something to you.

360
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:03,545
I like…

361
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,465
Wait, wait.

362
00:16:07,257 --> 00:16:08,342
Hold on a bit.

363
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:10,469
Just slow it down.

364
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:13,555
It's better if you court me first.

365
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:14,682
[in English] Exactly!

366
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:17,935
That's why I wanted to talk to you
before I start courting!

367
00:16:18,018 --> 00:16:21,605
I was thinking, maybe you have a tip,
because I want to court someone.

368
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:24,525
- [in English] Tip?
- Mmm-mmm.

369
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:26,360
Wait. Who are you courting?

370
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:30,698
Ah, okay, okay, okay.

371
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:32,032
[light music playing]

372
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:33,492
Are you all finished?

373
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:34,493
- [children] Yes!
- Not yet!

374
00:16:34,576 --> 00:16:35,411
Draw something--

375
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:37,246
- Not yet? Okay.
- Go ahead, it's fine.

376
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:39,623
[Cathy] Oh, wow! Yes!

377
00:16:39,707 --> 00:16:41,583
Us, the two of us?

378
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:43,419
That's so cute!

379
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:45,129
Let me see.

380
00:16:45,212 --> 00:16:46,255
There she is.

381
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:49,883
It's Cathy.

382
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:51,677
Let me see.

383
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:53,220
[mellow music playing]

384
00:16:53,303 --> 00:16:54,722
Oh, that's so cute!

385
00:16:54,805 --> 00:16:56,390
It looks really accurate.

386
00:17:00,894 --> 00:17:02,438
[in English] Do you see now, Karla?

387
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:05,149
She's the reason why I'm always here.

388
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:09,570
Wow! Amazing!

389
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:12,823
She's a volunteer worker
here in your barangay.

390
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:16,076
[in English] She helps a lot of kids.

391
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,661
[mellow music playing]

392
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:19,246
That's so sweet.

393
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:20,497
Wow!

394
00:17:22,082 --> 00:17:23,917
You know, Karla…

395
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,210
[in English] Cathy is my ideal girl.

396
00:17:25,794 --> 00:17:27,087
She's kind!

397
00:17:27,171 --> 00:17:29,381
See, she cares for those kids.

398
00:17:30,257 --> 00:17:31,216
Right?

399
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,260
I can clearly see it.

400
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:36,430
It's touching.

401
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:39,641
But…

402
00:17:40,642 --> 00:17:43,062
I just can't approach her because…

403
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:44,897
What, you're shy?

404
00:17:46,815 --> 00:17:48,108
[mellow music playing]

405
00:17:48,192 --> 00:17:49,526
[in English] Can I see, Lily?

406
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:51,612
- [T-Bak] Ah!
- [boy] Oh.

407
00:17:51,695 --> 00:17:53,405
[Cathy, in English] That's my car!

408
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:54,948
[Cathy] <i>My fog lamp got broken.</i>

409
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:58,911
I'll just take your ball as payment!

410
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:01,205
I'm sure you'll give it anyway, right?

411
00:18:01,288 --> 00:18:02,331
Thanks!

412
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:05,125
OMG! That's her!

413
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:06,794
You know her?

414
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:09,963
No, she just looks familiar.

415
00:18:10,047 --> 00:18:11,298
Ah.

416
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:16,303
You know, if I were you, Gavin?

417
00:18:16,386 --> 00:18:17,638
Don't confess yet.

418
00:18:19,139 --> 00:18:21,892
Make sure she's really the one you want.

419
00:18:21,975 --> 00:18:23,477
[light music playing]

420
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:25,062
Right. Right. You're right.

421
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:27,064
[in English] That's good advice.
Thank you.

422
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:30,317
Wait.

423
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:32,444
Why did you bring me here?

424
00:18:35,405 --> 00:18:37,074
I was wondering

425
00:18:38,075 --> 00:18:39,535
if you could help me…

426
00:18:39,618 --> 00:18:41,370
get closer to her?

427
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:44,665
I noticed she's drawn to…

428
00:18:45,999 --> 00:18:47,167
To the poor?

429
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:48,168
Like us?

430
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:50,129
From Tabang Lupa.

431
00:19:02,307 --> 00:19:03,851
[chuckles]

432
00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:06,436
- Hey, Emerson, what?
- [Emerson] Mmm? Mmm?

433
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:08,814
You're always eating here too?

434
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:11,441
You're too much. I even brought food!

435
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:13,777
I packed lunch. I'm shy too.

436
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,445
You're too much.

437
00:19:15,529 --> 00:19:17,072
And also…

438
00:19:18,073 --> 00:19:21,451
I thought it's lonely eating alone.

439
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:23,745
Since my sister's here,

440
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:25,080
I'll eat here too.

441
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,499
- Hmm.
- [Ame] Hmm?

442
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:29,918
- [in English] The more the merrier!
- [Emerson] Mmm-hmm.

443
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:32,588
- Right.
- At least Ibyang's in a good mood.

444
00:19:32,671 --> 00:19:34,131
Unlike someone else!

445
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:35,299
Who's that someone else?

446
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:36,967
Mom, just tired.

447
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:38,093
[Cita] Hmm?

448
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:42,681
Guess why I look excited.

449
00:19:42,764 --> 00:19:44,308
[Emerson] Why?

450
00:19:44,391 --> 00:19:46,018
[pleasant music playing]

451
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:49,104
Because Master and I are going
on a field trip next week!

452
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:50,147
- [Cita] Oh!
- [Emerson] Wow!

453
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:52,983
- [Emerson] Awesome.
- What? Did Atoy confirm with you?

454
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:54,359
Yes.

455
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:55,777
He even promised.

456
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:56,653
[Cita] Mmm.

457
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:59,406
He's the one who pretended
to be my dad at school!

458
00:19:59,489 --> 00:20:00,616
- [Cita] Oh?!
- [Tonet] Ayy!

459
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:02,451
- [Emerson] Wow!
- [Cita] Wow! Amazing!

460
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:05,370
Field trip, field trip!
Oh, that's exciting, baby.

461
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:07,164
Can Karla and I come too?

462
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:08,540
Hey.

463
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:10,083
Why am I dragged into this?

464
00:20:10,834 --> 00:20:12,044
That's fine!

465
00:20:12,127 --> 00:20:14,463
And Atoy will be there, right?

466
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:17,132
My beauty can't be missing there.

467
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:19,259
- What beauty?
- [Emerson] Hmm!

468
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:21,762
[Emerson laughs] What will you do there?

469
00:20:22,638 --> 00:20:24,014
[Karla] What are you gonna do there?

470
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:25,057
- That's my future, brother.
- Mmm.

471
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,308
[in English] That's my future!

472
00:20:26,391 --> 00:20:28,894
- [in English] Future? Future.
- What did your future say?

473
00:20:28,977 --> 00:20:30,562
Should Ame and I come too?

474
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,940
- Let's all go.
- [Karla] That's your future.

475
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:34,691
[music fades]

476
00:20:34,775 --> 00:20:36,151
[on screen] <i>That's so cute!</i>

477
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:37,778
<i>It looks really accurate.</i>

478
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:38,779
<i>You're amazing. Amazing, amazing.</i>

479
00:20:38,862 --> 00:20:39,863
[phone blips]

480
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:42,199
[in English] So, Audrey, great news.

481
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:43,992
We've found your child.

482
00:20:44,701 --> 00:20:46,119
[suspicious music playing]

483
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:49,039
Are you sure that's the child
you hid from me?

484
00:20:49,122 --> 00:20:50,332
Audrey,

485
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:53,877
I thought you'd be happy
with Martina's news.

486
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:57,631
[in English] My baby was taken from me.

487
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:01,927
[in English] I don't think you even have
the slightest idea how that feels.

488
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:05,973
[Gavin] But, Auntie, don't you want
to see the child?

489
00:21:07,182 --> 00:21:08,976
I just don't want false hope, Gavin.

490
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:11,228
[clears throat, in English]
You know, Audrey is right.

491
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:15,482
It's better to do
a DNA test first to be sure.

492
00:21:15,565 --> 00:21:18,026
[tense sinister music playing]

493
00:21:24,908 --> 00:21:25,993
- Oh.
- Oh, Karla,

494
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:28,495
what happened to your meeting earlier?

495
00:21:28,578 --> 00:21:29,788
Hey, yes.

496
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:31,415
Tonet told me about it.

497
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:33,292
So? Did Gavin confess?

498
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:35,711
No.

499
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:37,129
Lesson learned today.

500
00:21:37,212 --> 00:21:38,213
Don't assume.

501
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:40,048
[melancholic music playing]

502
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:42,551
Then why did he meet with you?

503
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:44,386
- [Ame] Mmm-hmm.
- [Karla] To ask for help to get closer

504
00:21:44,469 --> 00:21:46,179
to the girl he really likes.

505
00:21:46,263 --> 00:21:47,514
[Ame] Oh.

506
00:21:47,597 --> 00:21:49,599
So, do you know the girl?

507
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:54,438
Yes. The girl who took our basketball.

508
00:21:54,521 --> 00:21:57,274
I don't even know what he sees
in that plastic woman.

509
00:21:57,357 --> 00:21:59,192
- [Tonet] Oh.
- Such a bad attitude.

510
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:01,737
Let it go.

511
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:05,449
Sometimes there are things
that aren't meant for us.

512
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:07,284
[Tonet] Mmm.

513
00:22:07,367 --> 00:22:10,746
And there are also things

514
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:12,497
we really need to fight for.

515
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:14,041
Especially if we want them.

516
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:15,167
[Ame scoffs]

517
00:22:19,421 --> 00:22:21,465
[music fades]

518
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:31,683
[birds chirping]

519
00:22:36,396 --> 00:22:37,439
[in English] There you go!

520
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:38,523
[in English] It's done.

521
00:22:39,107 --> 00:22:39,941
[in English] Thank you, Doc.

522
00:22:40,025 --> 00:22:44,404
And I trust you'll speed up the results.

523
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:46,323
[in English] Of course, Dmitri.

524
00:22:46,406 --> 00:22:48,200
[in English] I'll put this
at the top of my list.

525
00:22:48,825 --> 00:22:51,578
Most probably, in five days,
we'll have the result.

526
00:22:51,661 --> 00:22:52,788
Thank you, Doc.

527
00:22:53,288 --> 00:22:54,289
Um…

528
00:22:54,372 --> 00:22:57,000
Will you also be the one to get
the sample from the child?

529
00:22:57,084 --> 00:23:01,171
Actually, I already sent my lab tech
with Martina to make it faster.

530
00:23:02,672 --> 00:23:04,007
[pensive music playing]

531
00:23:04,091 --> 00:23:07,052
All right, I'll bring this DNA sample
of the child to the doctor.

532
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:08,720
[in English] Thank you.

533
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:12,057
[suspicious music playing]

534
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:13,642
[titters]

535
00:23:13,725 --> 00:23:15,602
I don't get it.

536
00:23:15,685 --> 00:23:18,063
Why do you still need
a DNA test for the child?

537
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:22,943
Didn't you say she's your child,
that's why you took her back from me?

538
00:23:23,026 --> 00:23:26,988
Don't bother with those, Roma.

539
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:30,784
[in English] This is just,
you know, like a formality.

540
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:35,247
We just want to make sure
your expected payday won't be ruined.

541
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:36,289
Right?

542
00:23:39,668 --> 00:23:41,503
[music fades]

543
00:23:41,586 --> 00:23:44,923
[electronic blipping]

544
00:23:49,469 --> 00:23:51,805
[tense music playing]

545
00:23:51,888 --> 00:23:53,849
Welcome to your new home, grandchild.

546
00:23:53,932 --> 00:23:55,559
Will this be my house too?

547
00:23:55,642 --> 00:23:57,102
Say goodbye to your mother.

548
00:23:57,185 --> 00:23:59,104
She doesn't love me anyway.

549
00:23:59,187 --> 00:24:00,814
This brat.

550
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:03,150
I'm annoyed because of Master!

551
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:06,444
He said he can't come with me
tomorrow to the field trip!

552
00:24:06,528 --> 00:24:09,364
Maybe he has an important mission.

553
00:24:09,447 --> 00:24:12,200
You were about to leave the country
when your child was kidnapped?

554
00:24:12,284 --> 00:24:13,785
[in English] By my ex-husband.

555
00:24:13,869 --> 00:24:15,662
Will you be able to find my child?

556
00:24:15,745 --> 00:24:16,830
My tracker is good.

557
00:24:16,913 --> 00:24:18,206
[Atoy] <i>I've located the father and child.</i>

558
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:19,916
<i>I'll take care of this.</i>

559
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,751
<i>I'll find out when the father leaves,</i>

560
00:24:21,835 --> 00:24:23,461
<i>so I can find a window.</i>

561
00:24:23,545 --> 00:24:25,422
‪UP NEXT

562
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:29,885
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

563
00:24:31,845 --> 00:24:33,805
‪Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
